==English==

===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} [[hetero-]] (different) + [[klinein]] (to lean, inflect).

===Adjective===
'''heteroclite'''

# Deviating from the ordinary rule; eccentric.
#{{grammar}}: Being [[irregular]]ly [[decline]]d or [[inflect]]ed.

===Noun===
'''heteroclite'''

# A person who is unconventional; a maverick
#{{grammar}}: An [[irregular]]ly [[decline]]d or [[inflect]]ed [[word]]

